http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/BSNL-workers-seek-regularisation-of-services/article14011848.ece

The Karnataka State BSNL Non-Permanent Workers Union, affiliated to Centre for Indian Trade Union (CITU), on Wednesday staged a protest here demanding regularisation of their services and enhancement of their wages. L.R. Bhosle, district president of the union, in a memorandum addressed to the Leader of the Congress in the Lok Sabha M. Mallikarjun Kharge urged to take up the matter in the parliament session to resolve the long –pending problems of the BSNL non-permanent workers’.He added that the provident funds were not being deposited in the personal accounts of the workers regularly. Mr Bhosle alleged that they had been working for more than 12 hours a day without demanding extra wages and benefits such as revised minimum wages, paid weekly off, holidays and bonus which they are entitled.The Union government should consider the regularisation of contractual and outsourced workers serving for more than five years, equal pay for equal work, extend Provident Fund and pension facilities Mr. Bhosle added.